8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 61, L.D. 96, “An Act to Amend the
10 Motor Vehicles and Traffic Law Governing Mandatory Driver's License Suspension for
11 Refusing Testing for Drugs or a Combination of Drugs and Alcohol”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Amend the Motor Vehicle and Traffic Law Governing Administrative
14 Driver’s License Suspensions for Refusing Testing for Alcohol, Drugs or a
15 Combination of Drugs and Alcohol'
16 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
17 following:
18 'Sec. 1. 29-A MRSA §2401, sub-§5, as amended by PL 1995, c. 368, Pt. AAA, §4,
19 is further amended to read:
20 5. Failure to submit to a test, fails to submit to a test or failed to submit to a test.
21 "Failure to submit to a test," "fails to submit to a test" or "failed to submit to a test" means
22 failure to comply with the a duty under this chapter to submit to and complete a chemical
23 test under section 2521 or 2525 or tests to determine any presence or level of alcohol, to
24 determine any presence or level of any drug or drug metabolite or to determine any
25 presence or level of any combination of alcohol, drugs or drug metabolites. "Failure to
26 submit to a test," "fails to submit to a test" or "failed to submit to a test" does not include
27 failure to submit to and complete any standardized field sobriety testing.
28 Sec. 2. 29-A MRSA §2521, sub-§5, as enacted by PL 1993, c. 683, Pt. A, §2 and
29 affected by Pt. B, §5, is amended to read:
30 5. Suspension for refusal. The Secretary of State shall immediately suspend the
31 license of a person who had a duty under this chapter to submit to and complete a test or
32 tests to determine any presence or level of alcohol, to determine any presence or level of
33 any drug or drug metabolite or to determine any presence or level of any combination of
34 alcohol, drugs or drug metabolites and who fails to submit to and complete a the test or
35 tests.'
