COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 61, L.D. 96
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment, which is a minority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
55 changes the title. The amendment clarifies that definitions regarding failure to submit to
66 and complete a test apply to any test to determine any presence or level of alcohol, drugs
77 or drug metabolites, or any combination of those substances, with the exception of a
88 standardized field sobriety test. The amendment further requires the Secretary of State to
99 suspend the license of a person who had a duty to submit to and complete a test and failed
1100 to submit to or complete the test.
